io.damelyngdoh.java.trie

Class Trie<T extends TrieCharacter,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.damelyngdoh.java.trie.Trie<T,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of characters the trie will contain, must extends TrieCharacter class.
    V - The type of data which the Trie data-structure will contain in its nodes.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.util.List<TrieCharacter>,V>

    public class Trie<T extends TrieCharacter,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<java.util.List<TrieCharacter>,V>

    Trie class represents a Trie data-structure which saves, retrieves or removes strings which are a sequence of characters of type TrieCharacter. The vertices of the tree are represented by the TrieNode objects. The trie object contains a map object which represents the root node of the tree and contains mappings of TrieCharacter to TrieNode which are the initial characters of the strings added to the trie.

    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Dame Lyngdoh
